## The 3-level memory system

This workspace uses a layered memory architecture. Understanding it helps Claude help you better.

| Level | File | Scope | When it loads |
|---|---|---|---|
| Global | `CLAUDE.md` (this file) | Every session | Always |
| Role | `‹role›/memory/ROLE.md` | Within a role | SessionStart hook, when cwd is inside `‹role›/` |
| Project | `‹role›/‹project›/memory/PROJECT.md` | Within a project | You read it manually or it's referenced by ROLE.md |

**How to feed the system:**
- Tag insights inline in any `memory/PROJECT.md` using `[LESSON]:`, `[PATTERN]:`, `[GOTCHA]:`, `[TOOL]:`.
- The Stop hook scrapes these and queues them to `‹role›/memory/_pending.md`.
- Run `/role-promote ‹role›` to auto-reconcile the role brain (or it fires automatically when >7 days stale with pending activity).

**Org commands:**
- `/org-status` — see all roles, staleness, pending queues at a glance.
- `/new-project` — scaffold a new project under a role.
- `/role-promote ‹role›` — reconcile a role brain.
